from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    i = 0   # --- py stmt 3
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 4
    chars = set()   # --- py stmt 5
    for j, c in enumerate(s):   # --- py stmt 6
        if c == ' ':   # --- py stmt 7
            continue   # --- py stmt 8
        elif c == '*':   # --- py stmt 9
            break   # --- py stmt 10
        while c in chars:   # --- py stmt 11
            chars.remove(s[i])   # --- py stmt 12
            i += 1   # --- py stmt 13
        chars.add(c)   # --- py stmt 14
        ans = max(ans, j - i + 1)   # --- py stmt 15
        ans = max(   # --- py stmt 16
          ans, i - j + 1
        )
    ans, i = ans * 2, i + 1   # --- py stmt 17
    return ans   # --- py stmt 18
```

from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(nums: List[int]) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 3
    for i in range(31):   # --- py stmt 4
        a = b = 0   # --- py stmt 5
        for v in nums:   # --- py stmt 6
            t = (v >> i) & 1   # --- py stmt 7
            if t:   # --- py stmt 8
                a += 1   # --- py stmt 9
            else:   # --- py stmt 10
                b += 1   # --- py stmt 11
        ans += a * b   # --- py stmt 12
    return ans   # --- py stmt 13
```

function calculate_pairs_of_ones(nums) {   // --- py stmt 2
    var total_pairs = 0;   // --- py stmt 3
    for (var i = 0; i < 31; i++) {   // --- py stmt 4
        var zeros_count = 0;   // --- py stmt 5
        var ones_count = zeros_count;   // --- py stmt 5
        for (var v of nums) {   // --- py stmt 6
            var bit = (v >> i) & 1;   // --- py stmt 7

                ones_count += 1;   // --- py stmt 9
            }
            else {   // --- py stmt 10
                zeros_count += 1;   // --- py stmt 11
            }

        total_pairs += ones_count * zeros_count;   // --- py stmt 12
